# Security Policy

## Supported Versions

We release patches for security issues on the latest minor release line. Use the latest tag or `main` when possible.

| Version / branch | Supported          |
| ---------------- | -------------------- |
| Latest release   | :white_check_mark:   |
| Older tags       | :x: (upgrade advised) |

## Reporting a Vulnerability

**Please do not open a public GitHub issue for security reports.**

Instead, contact the maintainers privately:

- **Email:** {{ author_email }}
- **GitHub:** [@{{ github_username }}](https://github.com/{{ github_username }})

Include:

- A short description of the issue and its impact
- Steps to reproduce (if known)
- Any suggested fix or patch (optional)

We aim to acknowledge reports within a few business days and will coordinate disclosure once a fix is available.

Thank you for helping keep **{{ project_name }}** and its users safe.
